# Trivy ignore list for KubeBolt release scans.
#
# Policy: the release pipeline (.github/workflows/release.yml) fails on
# CRITICAL and HIGH severities. We pass --ignore-unfixed to Trivy so
# CVEs without an upstream patch never block a release. Anything that
# reaches this file is a deliberate, time-boxed exception.
#
# Format (one per line):
#   CVE-YYYY-NNNNN  # YYYY-MM-DD <owner> — why this is acceptable + remove-by date
#
# Required for every entry:
#   1. Owner (who decided to suppress).
#   2. Justification — why this CVE does not affect KubeBolt's runtime
#      (e.g. vulnerable package present but unreachable code path,
#      mitigated by network policy, etc.).
#   3. A remove-by date. Suppressions older than 90 days should be
#      reviewed; either the upstream fix has shipped (delete the line
#      and bump the image), or the justification needs renewal.
#
# Do NOT use this file to bypass scans because "the release is urgent".
# That defeats the entire purpose of the gate. Bump the vulnerable
# dependency or postpone the release.

# Bundled VictoriaMetrics / vmagent (v1.147.0 builds on Go 1.26.4). Both
# entries mirror kubebolt-ee's .trivyignore verbatim — same decision, same
# justification, same remove-by, so OSS and EE stay in sync.
CVE-2026-39822  # 2026-07-08 lmaina — os symlink+trailing-slash root-escape; VM is an internal metrics store that never resolves untrusted symlink paths in KubeBolt's deployment. Remove-by 2026-07-22 (bump VM to a Go-1.26.5+ build).
CVE-2026-42505  # 2026-07-08 lmaina — crypto/tls Encrypted Client Hello privacy leak; VM's TLS is intra-cluster and does not use ECH. Remove-by 2026-07-22 (bump VM to a Go-1.26.5+ build).
